<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A rectangular field has length <m>(x + {6})</m> metres and width <m>(x - {6})</m> metres.
(a) Express the area of the field as a simplified quadratic expression using a quadratic identity.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p>

<p>
(b) If <m>x = {14}</m>, find the area of the field.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans2"/>   <m>m^2</m>
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Area of a rectangle = length × width.
</p>

<p>
So the area is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {6})(x - {6})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Recognise the identity.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(a+b)(a-b) = a^2 - b^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Here,
</p>

<p>
<me>
a = x, \quad b = {6}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Apply the identity.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {6})(x - {6}) = x^2 - {36}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Substitute <m>x = {14}</m>.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 - {36} = {196} - {36}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {160}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the field is <alert><m>{160}</m> <m>m^2</m></alert>.
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2-36</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>160</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>